SIMPLE: supple
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Supple
<hw>Sup"ple</hw> <pr>(s⟦ucr⟧p"p'l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>souple</ets>, F. <ets>souple</ets>, from L. <ets>supplex</ets>
suppliant, perhaps originally, being the knees. Cf.
<er>Supplicate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Pliant; flexible; easily
bent; <as>as, <ex>supple</ex> joints; <ex>supple</ex>
fingers</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Yielding; compliant; not obstinate; submissive to
guidance; <as>as, a <ex>supple</ex> horse</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If punishment . . . makes not the will <qex>supple</qex>, it
hardens the offender.</q> <rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Bending to the humor of others; flattering; fawning;
obsequious.</def> <rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Pliant; flexible; yielding; compliant; bending;
flattering; fawning; soft.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supple</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Supple
<hw>Sup"ple</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Suppled</conjf> <pr>(s⟦ucr⟧p"p'ld)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Suppling</conjf> <pr>(s⟦ucr⟧p"pl⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To make soft and pliant; to render flexible; <as>as, to
<ex>supple</ex> leather</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The flesh therewith she <qex>suppled</qex> and did steep.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make compliant, submissive, or
obedient.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A mother persisting till she had bent her daughter's mind and
<qex>suppled</qex> her will.</q> <rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They should <qex>supple</qex> our stiff willfulness.</q>
<rj><qau>Barrow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supple</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Supple
<hw>Sup"ple</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become soft and
pliant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The stones . . . ⟦br⟧
<qex>Suppled</qex> into softness as they fell.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supple-chapped</ent>⟦br⟧
